parse: Verb - Future Indicative Middle - 3rd Person Plural
str2: A reduplicated and contracted form of peto; probably akin to petomai through the idea of alighting; to fall.
The mouth, speech, eloquence in speech, the point of a sword.
A sword. Probably feminine of a presumed derivative of mache; a knife, i.e. Dirk; figuratively, war, judicial punishment.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Passive - 3rd Person Plural
str2: To take captive (in war); I subdue, ensnare. From aichmalotos; to make captive.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
All, the whole, every kind of. Including all the forms of declension; apparently a primary word; all, any, every, the whole.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Probably from etho; a race, i.e. A tribe; specially, a foreign one.
Of Hebrew origin; Hierusalem, the capitol of Palestine.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Middle - 3rd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Middle or Passive - Nominative Feminine Singular
str2: To tread, trample upon. From a derivative probably of paio; to trample.
A primary preposition; under, i.e. of place, or with verbs; of place (underneath) or where (below) or time (when).
Probably from etho; a race, i.e. A tribe; specially, a foreign one.
As far as, up to, until, during. Or achris akh'-rece; akin to akron; until or up to.
Fitting season, season, opportunity, occasion, time. Of uncertain affinity; an occasion, i.e. Set or proper time.
Probably from etho; a race, i.e. A tribe; specially, a foreign one.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Passive - 3rd Person Plural
str2: From pleres; to make replete, i.e. to cram, level up, or to furnish, satisfy, execute, finish, verify, etc.
